title: JUI candidate Syed Zafar Ali Agha wins PB-49
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamiat Ullema-e-Islam (JUI) candidate Syed Zafar Ali Agha won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-49, Pishin-III by securing 13,811 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pashtunkhawa Mili Awami Party candidate Agha Syed Liaqat Ali who bagged 12,778 votes.
Over-all votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 38.00 per cent.
